______________
   
      Menus
   ___________


   File

      Open..       -   Select one or more files to open.
                       Already opened documents will not be trashed.
                       Duplicate file names will bring up a requester.
      
      Insert..     -   Select one or more files to insert into current document,
                        at cursor position.

      Save         -   Save current document without file-requester.

      Save As..    -   Save current document with file-requester.
                       If file already exists, a requester will pop up. 

      Quit         -   Exit program. 
                       If there are edited but unsaved documents,
                        a requester will appear.

   Edit

      Cut          -   Cut out currently marked area of the text and place 
                        in buffer.

      Copy         -   Copy currently marked area of the text into buffer.

      Paste        -   Paste current buffer into text.

      Del Line     -   Delete current line in text.

      Del To EOL   -   Delete all characters from cursor to end of line.

      Lower Case   -   Change case of all characters currently marked, to low.

      Upper Case   -   Change case of all characters currently marked, to up.

      Flip Case    -   Toggle case of all characters currently marked.

   Document

      Close        -   Close current document.
                       If document is edited but unsaved, a requester will appear.
                       (There can never be less than one document open at any 
                         time, closing the last document will just clear it and
                         rename it to "unnamed".)

      Next         -   Bring up next document in list of open documents.
                       Does nothing if there is only one document.

      New          -   Create a new document. Its name will be:
                        "<previous document path>unnamed".

      <documents>  -   A list of all open documents. Last opened/selected on top.

   Find

      Search..     -   Brings up a window to define what to search for in the text.

      Replace..    -   Brings up a window to define what to replace in the text.

      Search Next  -   Continiue searching forward.

      Replace      -   Replace text at the cursor now.

   Tools
   
      Compile      -   Compile current document (source). 
                       If there was errors, the compilation window will appear.
                        (see below)
                       
      Compilation..-   Brings up the compilation window.
                       From here compilation may be done,
                       setting compiler parameters, 
                       view compiler output,
                       click on error(s) to make cursor jump to it.

      Run          -   Run current executable. Nothing will happen if there
                       is no executable.

      Run Args..   -   Run current executable with arguments. 
      
      Result       -   Opens the compiler output log file.
                                        
      Proc List    -   Display a sorted list of procedures in a window.
                       Selecting procedure makes cursor jump to 
                       that procedure in the text. Methods are supported too.

      Label Doc    -   Start external command to search for information on
                       the label in source, currently pointed to by cursor.
      
      Debug..      -   Start (external) debugger.                    
                       
   Prefs
   
      Colours..    -   Brings up colour preferences window.
      
      General..    -   Brings up general preferences window.
      
      MUI..        -   Brings up MUI settings window.
      
      Save         -   Save Program Settings.
                                                                                
   Help
   
      About Insomnia.. - Display information about Insomnia.
      
      About MUI..  -   Brings up the About MUI window.
      
      <usercommands> - Here userdefined helpcommands may be selected.
      
   Paths
   
      <filedirs>   -   List of visited directories. 
                       Selecting a directory will bring up the 
                       open-file requester.
                       
                                 
                                                                                        
